      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I believe removing boost header includes should continue for the following reasons:\r\n\r\n* `std::thread` in C++11 is mostly identical to `std::thread` in C++17. So when we reach C++17, we better have alreay dealt with removing `boost::thread*`, so that the only remaining things are fs and the optional/unique_ptr utils.\r\n* Apart from `serialize.h`, the boost headers are the most memory and cpu hungry to compile\r\n* Depending on less third party modules during the build is a \"nice to have\"",
      "created_at" : "2019-11-01T12:49:32Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/17307#issuecomment-548776175",
      "id" : 548776175,
